READ AND WRITE TO ANOTHER FILE - o/p annotated with line numbers
------------------------------

import com.twitter.scalding._

val input=TextLine("data/a.txt")
val output=TextLine("data/b.txt")
input.read.write(output)

--=====================================
just to write the data alone from above case

input.read..project('line).write(output)

scalding functions divided into 4 types - map like fns - grouping fns - group/reduce operns - join operns

Map like fns - map, flatmap, mapTo, flatMapTo, project, discard, insert, rename, limit, filter, filterNot, unique, pack, unpack

Grouping fnd - groupBy, groupAll(single reducer)

Group/Reduce operns - .size, .average(field), .sum(field), .count(field){fn}, .sortBy(fields), pivot, unpivot

Joins - joinWithSmaller, joinWithLarger - joinWithTiny
